[SN]TITLE[SN]
FC Halifax Town 4-2 Grimsby Town

[SN]FIRST-SENTENCE[SN]
Halifax moved out of the National League relegation zone with a stunning victory over high-flying Grimsby.

[SN]RESTBODY[SN]
Billy Whitehouse's debut goal, James Bolton's driven effort and Nicky Wroe's cool finish gave the home side a surprise three-goal lead at half-time.
Padraig Amond gave the visitors hope late on before Jake Hibbs placed one into the top corner to restore the two-goal cushion.
The Mariners' Jon Nolan smashed in a late consolation as Halifax held on.
Grimsby Town manager Paul Hurst told BBC Radio Humberside:
